title: For Sale:  Custom Remington 700 7mm STW 26" Broughton 416R SS
postcontent:
This is a freshly built custom Remington 700 chambered for 7mm STW. This rifle was built with an emphasis on accuracy by competitive benchrest shooter Pete Piper of Precision Barrel Work in Hempstead, Texas. The heart of this rifle is a 26" Broughton 5c 416R Stainless Steel Match barrel with a 1:9" twist rate. Broughton barrels are double stress relieved at the mill and triple stress relieved in the shop, pulled button-rifles, and hand lapped with a uniform land and groove diameter up to .0001" from breech to muzzle. The barrel is straight fluted for decreased weight and increased heat dispersion, is threaded with a custom left hand helical muzzle brake fitted, and finally matte black cerakoted for a consistent appearance and durable longevity.
The receiver is completely trued, has a 1.070" thread tennon, and is pillar bedded in an epoxy gel to extract maximum accuracy. A Jewell trigger set to ~2 pounds further enhances potential precision. The bolt body is spiral fluted for decreased contact area, increasing the smoothness of cycling, and lending a high end custom look.
This rifle features a McMillan Hunter stock with grip and forend checkering and a Pachmayr Decelerator buttpad. It has an olive drab green, tan, and black marbled matte finish.
This rifle is built on a used receiver, so I have technically listed the item condition as used, however it has it is for all intents and purposes new. Please feel free to email me with specific inquirie
